`inner (v_j) (A * v_j) = inner (v_j) (λ_j * v_j) = λ_j * inner (v_j) (v_j) = λ_j * ||v_j||^2`.

Since `v_j` is a unit vector (because it's part of an orthonormal basis), `||v_j||^2 = 1`. Therefore, `inner (v_j) (A * v_j) = λ_j`. The real part of this is just `λ_j`.

